      "translation": "The primary impact of the pandemic on our 2020 financial performance was on new business sales, as containment measures in many of our markets restricted face-to-face sales activities, particularly in the first half of 2020. Although VONB of US$2,765 million in 2020 was 33% lower than in 2019, we rapidly adopted new digital tools and the general easing of movement restrictions supported a recovery in sales momentum. AIA China was the largest contributor to the Group's VONB in 2020 and was our first reporting segment to show a recovery in sales momentum, as the region progressively eased strict lockdowns from March 2020. Excluding Mainland China visitor sales to Hong Kong, which remained at low levels, VONB across our other segments recovered strongly in the second half, growing 23% compared to the first half..."
